The paper discusses accountability in cyber-physical systems, which involves security and safety concerns (cs.CR), as well as software engineering (cs.SE) and system design (cs.SY). The use of a formal model suggests a focus on formal methods and verification (cs.CY), while the demonstration of different interpretations of accountability suggests a potential application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
